<!-- Workflow configuration -->
<!--
    Chain of Responsibility is a behavioral design pattern that begins a workflow and lets you pass
    requests along a chain of commands. Upon receiving a request, each command decides either to
    process the request or to pass it to the next command in the chain.
    
    Thus a Chain may have multiple Commands. Every command has the ability to backtrack in case of
    any error. Although this is not a mandatory behaviour.
    
    While specifying the set of commands for a particular workflow chain user must mention the order
    in which the commands will be executed within a chain.
    
    1. engine - The workflow engine. This is the core of COR pattern.
    
    2. chain  - Name of the workflow chain. Every chain has multiple commands.
        2.1 name  - Name of the command (must be unique).
        2.2 class - Fully qualified command class name (must be a sub-class of Command interface).
        2.3 order - Execution order of this command within a chain.
        2.4 backtrack - Indicates whether backtracking is enabled in this command.
-->
